AGENT ConstitutionalOSShield
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 4
PURPOSE Constitutional OS protection daemon that monitors process behavior against learned manifolds and escalates through sovereign levels on boundary violations
GOAL Observe process behavior via psutil snapshots, compute constitutional distance
     from learned baselines, escalate through L1-L4 sovereign response levels with
     false-positive confidence gating, and maintain HMAC-signed audit log

RECEIVES process_snapshot: ProcessSnapshot
EMITS escalation_event: dict, shield_log_entry: dict
MUTATES axiom_os_shield_log.jsonl
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, safety_ceiling, learning_window_hours,
             l1_threshold, l2_threshold, l3_threshold, l4_threshold,
             fp_l1_cutoff, fp_l2_cutoff, fp_l3_cutoff

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 4 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT SAFETY_CEILING is 0.25 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT LEARNING_WINDOW_HOURS is 72 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT L1_THRESHOLD is 0.06 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT L2_THRESHOLD is 0.04 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT L3_THRESHOLD is 0.02 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT L4_THRESHOLD is 0.005 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT FP_L1_CUTOFF is 0.40 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT FP_L2_CUTOFF is 0.70 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT FP_L3_CUTOFF is 0.90 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT All escalation events are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT FP calibration cannot widen manifold beyond SAFETY_CEILING
CONSTRAINT L4 escalation is immediate and not gated by FP confidence
CONSTRAINT Kernel access attempts always trigger L4 regardless of distance

RULES
- On establish_baseline: observe process via psutil for duration and record behavioral profile
- On measure_distance: compare current snapshot to baseline and emit constitutional distance 0.0 to 1.0
- On distance below L1_THRESHOLD: compute FP confidence and escalate if above FP_L1_CUTOFF
- On distance below L2_THRESHOLD: compute FP confidence and escalate if above FP_L2_CUTOFF
- On distance below L3_THRESHOLD: compute FP confidence and escalate if above FP_L3_CUTOFF
- On distance below L4_THRESHOLD: escalate immediately without FP gating
- On kernel access attempt detected: escalate to L4 immediately regardless of distance
- On L1 escalation: log event and flag for review
- On L2 escalation: throttle process and notify administrator
- On L3 escalation: suspend process pending human review
- On L4 escalation: kill process immediately
- On FP calibration: review last 24 hours of L1 events and widen manifold if pattern repeats 3 or more days
- On FP calibration widen: constrain new threshold to not exceed SAFETY_CEILING

PROCESS
- ConstitutionalOSShield is instantiated with manifests directory and learning mode flag
- ProcessManifold is created per monitored process with baseline behavioral profile
- All monitored processes are snapshotted every 500ms via psutil
- Each snapshot is compared to the process manifold baseline
- Constitutional distance is computed as normalized deviation from baseline
- Distance below threshold triggers FP confidence computation
- FP confidence combines historical FP rate and ancestry anomaly and trajectory consistency
- Escalation level is determined by distance threshold crossed and FP confidence gate
- All events are HMAC signed and appended to axiom_os_shield_log.jsonl
- FP calibration runs periodically to tune manifold without exceeding SAFETY_CEILING

CHECK
- Ransomware enumeration pattern triggers L3 or higher escalation
- Privilege escalation ancestry chain triggers L2 or higher escalation
- Kernel access attempt triggers L4 escalation immediately
- Antivirus scan with high file access does not trigger escalation above L1
- Software update with self-modification does not trigger escalation above L1
- Developer build with high CPU and process spawn does not trigger escalation
- SAFETY_CEILING assignment raises AttributeError
- L4_THRESHOLD assignment raises AttributeError
- FP_L1_CUTOFF assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- process_anomaly_detected: activate ManifoldDistanceCheck
- learning_window_active: activate BaselineCalibration
- fp_calibration_due: activate FalsePositiveCalibration

FAILURE
- On psutil access denied: log warning and skip process without crashing
- On missing baseline for process: enter learning mode for that process
- On log write error: log warning but do not fail the escalation

CONCEPT ManifoldDistanceCheck
PURPOSE Compute constitutional distance between current process behavior and learned baseline
APPLIES WHEN process snapshot deviates from established manifold
NOT WHEN process is in learning window or explicitly whitelisted
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES ProcessSnapshot and established ProcessManifold baseline
EFFECT Constitutional distance computed and escalation triggered if below threshold

CONCEPT BaselineCalibration
PURPOSE Learn normal process behavior during initial observation window
APPLIES WHEN process is first seen or learning mode is active
NOT WHEN learning window has expired and baseline is established
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES psutil process access and observation duration
EFFECT ProcessManifold baseline established with behavioral profile

CONCEPT FalsePositiveCalibration
PURPOSE Tune manifold thresholds based on historical false positive patterns
APPLIES WHEN FP rate for a process exceeds acceptable level over 3 or more days
NOT WHEN calibration would widen manifold beyond SAFETY_CEILING
PRIORITY 3
REQUIRES Historical L1 event log for the process
EFFECT Manifold widened within SAFETY_CEILING constraint

OUTPUT
- escalation_event: dict with level, process_name, pid, distance, fp_confidence, action, signature
- shield_log_entry: dict with timestamp, event_type, process_name, distance, signature

SUCCESS
ransomware_detected:           0.20
privilege_escalation_detected: 0.15
kernel_access_blocked:         0.15
antivirus_not_blocked:         0.15
update_not_blocked:            0.10
developer_not_blocked:         0.10
cannot_mutate_enforced:        0.10
hmac_signature_valid:          0.05
